isgVGIsdnCfgChanTable.name: isgVGIsdnCfgChanTable
isgVGIsdnCfgChanTable.description: This table contains ISDN Channel Configuration parameters.

isgVGIsdnCfgChanTableEntry.name: isgVGIsdnCfgChanTableEntry
isgVGIsdnCfgChanTableEntry.description: An ISDN Channel Configuration Table Entry.

isgVGIsdnCfgEntryNum.name: isgVGIsdnCfgEntryNum
isgVGIsdnCfgEntryNum.description: This indicates the Channel Configuration Table Entry Number.

isgVGIsdnCfgDChanPort.name: isgVGIsdnCfgDChanPort
isgVGIsdnCfgDChanPort.description: The associated port for the ISDN D-channel. dchanzero : Both B channels have access type Permanent. No D Channel data. dchanone : Packet Data on D-channel (Port 1 Type = X25) or B-channel access type is Switched type. dchanfour : Packet Data on D-Channel (Port 4 Type = X25). nc : Skipped during configuration.

isgVGIsdnCfgSwitchType.name: isgVGIsdnCfgSwitchType
isgVGIsdnCfgSwitchType.description: Specifies switch type for the central office. bri1tr6Stype : German National ISDN. bri5essStype : AT&T switch briDms100Stype : DMS 100. briKddStype : Japanese International Access ISDN. briEtsiStype : Euro ISDB BRI (NET3). briNi1Stype : National ISDN version 1. briNttStype : Japanese National ISDN. briTs013Stype : Australian National ISDN. briVnStype : France National ISDN.

isgVGIsdnCfgDChanTEI.name: isgVGIsdnCfgDChanTEI
isgVGIsdnCfgDChanTEI.description: The Terminal Endpoint Identifier value is provided by the service provider. The range for TEI is 0..63, 127, 255. If the Switch Type is configured as DMS-1, the possible range for TEI selection will be limited to 1..63. If TEI is configured to 255, the next valid TEI will be used and if TEI is configured to 127, automatic TEI negotiation will take place.

isgVGIsdnCfgDPckTraffic.name: isgVGIsdnCfgDPckTraffic
isgVGIsdnCfgDPckTraffic.description: enable : Signalling and X.25 data over the D Channel. disable : Only signalling data over the D Channel.

isgVGIsdnCfgDChanDN.name: isgVGIsdnCfgDChanDN
isgVGIsdnCfgDChanDN.description: Local Subscriber Directory Number (DN) DN is provided by the ISDN service provider.

isgVGIsdnCfgDSPID.name: isgVGIsdnCfgDSPID
isgVGIsdnCfgDSPID.description: The Service Profile ID identifies the service profile and is provided by the ISDN service provider.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstBChanPort.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstBChanPort
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstBChanPort.description: 0 : No call or TEI activity for the following objects prefixed by `isgVGIsdnCfgFirst' 1-3 : The associated port whose traffic will be on the ISDN B-channel which has the call and TEI objects prefixed by `isgVGIsdnCfgFirst'.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstAccType.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstAccType
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstAccType.description: perm : Dedicated (nailed-down) B-channel service. cmd : Dialed B-channel service: Circuit Mode. pmd : Dialed B-channel service: Packet Mode. cvl : Dialed B-channel service: Circuit Mode (Virtual Leased Line). dov : dialed B-channel service: Circuit Mode (Data over voice).

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstCallDisablSTm.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstCallDisablSTm
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstCallDisablSTm.description: The Call Disable Start Time indicates whether ISDN calls will/will-not be blocked. This field is blank or displayed in the format `HHMM'. blank : ISDN calls will not be blocked. HHMM : ISDN calls will be blocked starting at HH hour MM minutes.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstCallEnablSTm.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstCallEnablSTm
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstCallEnablSTm.description: The Call Enable Start Time indicates whether ISDN calls will/will-not be blocked. This field is blank or displayed in the format `HHMM'. blank : ISDN calls will not be blocked. HHMM : ISDN calls will be blocked starting at HH hour MM minutes.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBU.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBU
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBU.description: This port is configured to carry Same Port Backup (SPBU) feature. This feature requires the corresponding Port's Connection Type be SIMP.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBUOpt.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBUOpt
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBUOpt.description: Same Port Backup (SPBU) feature options This defines the switch back criteria for the backup ISDN line. NONE : No SPBU feature options. TIMEOUT : Based on a pre-configured timeout period. CALL : Based on the status of the Backup ISDN call. Any combination of the above can be specified by summing (e.g. TIMEOUT+CALL).

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBUTmOut.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBUTmOut
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPBUTmOut.description: Same Port Backup (SPBU) Timeout Counter. This defines the ISDN call duration time before a return to the leased line is attempted. This parameter is valid when TIMEOUT option is selected. The timeout period is a 1 minute interval.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstRate.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstRate
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstRate.description: This parameter specifies the line speed for this channel. rate64k : No Adaptation rate128k : Bonded, no adaptation rate56k : Rate Adapted to 64K rate112k : Rate Adapted to 12D8K.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstTEI.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstTEI
isgVGIsdnCfgFirstTEI.description: The value for the TEI (Terminal Endpoint Identifier). is provided by the service provider. The range is 0..63, 127, 255. Select 127 for automatic TEI negotiation and 255 to use Packet D TEI.

isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPID.name: isgVGIsdnCfgFirstSPID
